Each module must have a REAL implementation:
- `layer.msg()`: Creates a toast div, auto-fades after 2s. Supports icon option (1=success green, 2=error red, 5=sad, 6=happy).
- `layer.confirm()`: Creates a modal with Yes/No buttons, calls callbacks.
- `layer.open()`: Creates modal with title, content (can be HTML string), area (width/height), btn array.
- `layer.close()`: Removes modal by index.
- `layer.load()`: Shows loading spinner overlay.
- `form.render()`: Re-processes form elements (selects, checkboxes, radios) to add Layui styling.
- `form.on('submit(filter)', callback)`: Hooks form submit events.
- `form.verify()`: Registers custom validation rules.
- `laypage.render()`: Creates pagination HTML with page numbers, prev/next, calls jump callback.
- `laydate.render()`: Creates a simple date+time picker attached to an input element.
- `upload.render()`: Creates file input with drag-drop zone, validates file types and sizes, calls done/error callbacks.
- `rate.render()`: Creates clickable star rating widget.
- `element.on('tab(filter)', callback)`: Handles tab switching.

